OL,3,CMillions of workers to get new rights
OL,4,Cfrom day one in job under new law
OL,6,FThere are still a number of areas
OL,7,Fwhere tension remains, particularly
OL,8,Faround the definition of
OL,9,F"exploitative" zero-hour contracts,
OL,10,Fand the length of a probation period
OL,11,Fwhich would allow businesses to
OL,12,Fdismiss people "fairly".
OL,14,FMost of the reforms being put forward
OL,15,Fin the new law won't come into effect
OL,16,Ffor around two years - the government
OL,17,Fsay they will hold consultations on
OL,18,Fmany of the measures, and that some
OL,19,Fsecondary legislation will also need
OL,20,Fto be introduced as the Bill
OL,21,Fprogresses.
