OL,4,Cfrom day one in job under new law
OL,6,FFlexible working will be made the
OL,7,Fdefault position "where practical",
OL,8,Fwhile large employers will be required
OL,9,Fto create action plans on addressing
OL,10,Fany gender pay gaps.
OL,12,FWhen Labour first announced their
OL,13,Fflagship plan to reform worker's
OL,14,Frights, they promised to ban zero-hour
OL,15,Fcontracts entirely.
OL,17,FBut they later changed the wording of
OL,18,Fthat promise to only ban
OL,19,F"exploitative" zero-hour contracts, to
OL,20,Fthe frustration of many unions.
